ts to work properly. It's essential to provide clear guidance instead of taking no action.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Determining setup requirements**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to represent dependencies and Docker images as entries for deterministic setup. It's important to put environment variables and other test setups into agent guidance without repeating deterministic entries. I should consider if creating a temporary git repository is necessary, even though that setup likely excludes test fixtures. Also, for the maven-scm-provider-gitexe, it seems that a Git executable is necessary, but not as a Docker image. I'll need to explore existing upstream tests to see if including the `maven-scm-provider-gittest` dependency is essential for meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing test dependency needs**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the existing tests don’t include certain aspects, and the test fixture library has necessary helpers. I'm considering whether to add an extra Maven dependency for the generator. It might be possible to reuse Maven SCM's own testing harness for setting up a repository, but I typically want to avoid adding unnecessary test dependencies. Perhaps JDK ProcessBuilder could work for initializing the git repository, but I need to check the documentation about using the checkout feature through the provider.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RevT0XTiMdkcYgQ0MGyFknay|fc_084678661acd3324016a2a3ccb28948190b5072bad60a75a4f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nurls=['https://maven.apache.org/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/index.html','https://maven.apache.org/scm/git.html','https://maven.apache.org/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/']\nfor url in urls:\n print('\\nURL', url)\n try:\n  text=urllib.request.urlopen(url,timeout=10).read().decode('utf-8','replace')\n  # strip tags crude\n  body=re.sub('<script.*?</script>','',text,flags=re.S)\n  body=re.sub('<style.*?</style>','',body,flags=re.S)\n  body=re.sub('<[^>]+>',' ',body)\n  body=re.sub(r'\\s+',' ',body)\n  for term in ['Git CLI','Git Executable','git command','SCM Git']:\n    i=body.lower().find(term.lower())\n    if i!=-1: print(body[max(0,i-300):i+500])\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1161, "output": 1265, "cacheRead": 40448, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42874, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781152941846, "responseId": "resp_084678661acd3324016a2a3cae82188190b0e637d992257195"}}
