ms like the implementation of the artifact may need a direct import, avoiding unnecessary dependencies. I want to make sure I provide thorough guidance and clarify if there's no extra setup needed for certain actions. Also, it’s important to keep risks in mind regarding real git usage and external dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying meaningful coverage**\\n\\nI’m exploring how to provide meaningful coverage using command factories and consumers without executing git, which is tricky since there’s a local git executable available in CI but it doesn't guarantee a deterministic setup. There’s no Maven dependency needed, and Docker isn’t necessary either. I’m considering if I should configure the git user in local temp repos through test setup guidance. Also, I need to be careful about when I advise on setup, particularly regarding environment variables or additional dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Determining setup requirements**\\n\\nFor meaningful coverage when generated tests need to invoke check-in or tagging, it looks like git does require an identity. The normal generated test scaffold should be able to write Java code to run `git config user.email` using ProcessBuilder. This setup is essential for the tests to perform before achieving meaningful coverage. I need to think about the three types of setup: environment/system properties and how they differ from arbitrary test code. I should consider if any additional setup is necessary before reaching that coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing library setup needs**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the library requires any setup beyond the normal generated test scaffold. It seems that meaningful coverage relies on having an actual git repository, which isn’t deterministic. I need to check if the agent should be advised on this. The setup could involve an extra Maven dependency, a Docker image, or an environment/system property for the tests to work properly. It's essential to provide clear guidance instead of taking no action.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Determining setup requirements**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to represent dependencies and Docker images as entries for deterministic setup. It's important to put environment variables and other test setups into agent guidance without repeating deterministic entries. I should consider if creating a temporary git repository is necessary, even though that setup likely excludes test fixtures. Also, for the maven-scm-provider-gitexe, it seems that a Git executable is necessary, but not as a Docker image. I'll need to explore existing upstream tests to see if including the `maven-scm-provider-gittest` dependency is essential for meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing test dependency needs**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the existing tests don’t include certain aspects, and the test fixture library has necessary helpers. I'm considering whether to add an extra Maven dependency for the generator. It might be possible to reuse Maven SCM's own testing harness for setting up a repository, but I typically want to avoid adding unnecessary test dependencies. Perhaps JDK ProcessBuilder could work for initializing the git repository, but I need to check the documentation about using the checkout feature through the provider.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RevT0XTiMdkcYgQ0MGyFknay|fc_084678661acd3324016a2a3ccb28948190b5072bad60a75a4f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nurls=['https://maven.apache.org/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/index.html','https://maven.apache.org/scm/git.html','https://maven.apache.org/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/']\nfor url in urls:\n print('\\nURL', url)\n try:\n  text=urllib.request.urlopen(url,timeout=10).read().decode('utf-8','replace')\n  # strip tags crude\n  body=re.sub('<script.*?</script>','',text,flags=re.S)\n  body=re.sub('<style.*?</style>','',body,flags=re.S)\n  body=re.sub('<[^>]+>',' ',body)\n  body=re.sub(r'\\s+',' ',body)\n  for term in ['Git CLI','Git Executable','git command','SCM Git']:\n    i=body.lower().find(term.lower())\n    if i!=-1: print(body[max(0,i-300):i+500])\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1161, "output": 1265, "cacheRead": 40448, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42874, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781152941846, "responseId": "resp_084678661acd3324016a2a3cae82188190b0e637d992257195"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_RevT0XTiMdkcYgQ0MGyFknay|fc_084678661acd3324016a2a3ccb28948190b5072bad60a75a4f", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\nURL https://maven.apache.org/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/index.html\n Skins Components Archetype Artifact Resolver Doxia Indexer JXR Plugin Testing Plugin Tools Resource Bundles SCM Shared Components Surefire Wagon ASF How Apache Works Foundation Data Privacy Sponsoring Apache Thanks About Maven SCM Git Provider - Git Executable Impl. SCM Git Provider relying on the Git CLI © 2003–2025 The Apache Software Foundation \n About – Maven SCM Git Executable Apache / Maven / Apache Maven SCM / Maven SCM Providers / Maven SCM Git Provider / Maven SCM Git Executable / About | Last Published: 2025-09-19 Version: 2.2.1 Parent Project Maven SCM Git Provider - Parent Overview Introduction JavaDocs Source Xref Project Documentation Project Information About Summary Maven Coordinates Team Source Code Management Issue Management Mailing Lists Dependency Management Dependencies Dependency Convergence CI Management Plugin Management Plugins Dist\n About – Maven SCM Git Executable Apache / Maven / 